                                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[10 Hidden macOS 26 Features That Are Worth Upgrading For]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/hidden-macos-26-features-that-are-worth-upgrading-for/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Tim Brookes]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/macos-taho-logo.jpg" length="2246" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Mac]]></category><category><![CDATA[macOS]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple]]></category><category><![CDATA[Shortcuts]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            There’s more to see than Liquid Glass and desktop widgets.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>You can finally upgrade to macOS 26 on supported Mac models, just head to System Settings > General > Software Update and click the “Upgrade” button. Some features, like app overhauls and the Liquid Glass facelift, are obvious. Others are buried deep within menus.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 16 Sep 2025 12:00:18 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/hidden-macos-26-features-that-are-worth-upgrading-for/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Scene Stealers—12 of TV’s Most Memorable Supporting Characters]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/televisions-most-memorable-supporting-characters/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Keeley Brooks]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/collage-featuring-klaus-from-the-umbrella-academy-liv-baker-from-resident-alien-and-masuka-from-dexter-1.png" length="2400" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Streaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[TV Shows]]></category><category><![CDATA[Video Streaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[Netflix]]></category><category><![CDATA[Hulu]]></category><category><![CDATA[Amazon Prime Video]]></category><category><![CDATA[HBO Max]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Hey! These supporting characters matter, too!
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>I love movies, but when it comes to television, I can’t get enough. While I’m always down to explore genres and hop down the rabbit-hole of various plots, I love noticing all things outside the main spotlight, like supporting characters. Oftentimes, they’re responsible for driving a story to a certain end or carrying part of a narrative, whereas other times, they make a series completely.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 16 Sep 2025 11:30:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/televisions-most-memorable-supporting-characters/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[I’ve Never Used a Vacuum That Moved This Easily, and It Mops Floors Too]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/dreame-h15-pro-carpetflex-review/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Chris Hachey]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/09/dreame-4.jpg" length="209" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Smart Home]]></category><category><![CDATA[Dreame H15 Pro CarpetFlex]]></category><category><![CDATA[Dreame]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            This handled all kinds of spills better than I expected.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Messes happen, and it can be hard to keep all of your floors clean. Whether you have hardwood, tile, throw rugs, plush carpet, or linoleum, there's not always a one-size-fits-all way to keep them all clean. You probably need multiple ways to clean each one. The solution may be a 2-in-1 floor cleaner, such as the <a href="https://www.dreametech.com/products/h15-pro-carpetflex-wet-dry-vacuum?irclickid=zYk161UO2xycRWuUAjXCDSPOUkpwoBX5RQh-3c0&irgwc=1&UTM_source=affiliate&UTM_medium=impact&Partner=ICUBESWIRE%20TECHNOLOGY%20MENA%20FZLLC&Partner_ID=2615427" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Dreame H15 Pro CarpetFlex</a>.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 16 Sep 2025 10:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/dreame-h15-pro-carpetflex-review/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Google Search Just Broke This Hidden Feature]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/google-search-just-broke-this-hidden-feature/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Corbin Davenport]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/new-google-logo.jpg" length="93" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Web]]></category><category><![CDATA[Google]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Whoops.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Google Search has many hidden settings and search parameters that customize results pages. Unfortunately, one of them is no longer working reliably, and might be removed entirely in the future: the “num” option.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 15 Sep 2025 22:35:58 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/google-search-just-broke-this-hidden-feature/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[4 Hobbies Perfect for Cutting Your Screen Time]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/hobbies-perfect-for-cutting-your-screen-time/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Sydney Butler]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/flat-lay-of-a-phone-with-an-hourglass-beside-it-a-mechanical-keyboard-a-ham-radio-a-telescope-lens-and-rpg-dice.png" length="1898" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Hobbies]]></category><category><![CDATA[Gaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[Retro Gaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[Astronomy]]></category><category><![CDATA[DIY]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Because we all need a break from the pixels.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>A lot of pastimes now involve staring at a screen, and while I'm the last person to comment on what "too much" screen time is, I've found myself <em>not </em>wanting to look at a screen more often these days. Which, considering what a geek I am, doesn't mean I want to take up hiking or meditation.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 15 Sep 2025 22:00:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/hobbies-perfect-for-cutting-your-screen-time/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[I Can't Decide if Smart Typewriters Are Dumb or Brilliant]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/i-cant-decide-if-smart-typewriters-are-dumb-or-brilliant/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Sydney Butler]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2023/12/freewrite-alpha-from-the-side-with-the-kickstand-engaged.JPG" length="594" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Hobbies]]></category><category><![CDATA[Freewrite Alpha]]></category><category><![CDATA[Productivity]]></category><category><![CDATA[laptops]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            I guess it's just not my type.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>As someone who writes for a living—between 5,000 and 10,000 words every day—I'm always looking for ways to become more productive and efficient. Which is why I ran across a class of device I never thought I'd see—smart typewriters.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 15 Sep 2025 21:30:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/i-cant-decide-if-smart-typewriters-are-dumb-or-brilliant/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Why Streaming Subtitles Are Always Slightly Wrong]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/why-streaming-subtitles-are-always-slightly-wrong/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Sydney Butler]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/shutterstock_1331135633.jpg" length="479" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Streaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[Anime]]></category><category><![CDATA[Netflix]]></category><category><![CDATA[DVD]]></category><category><![CDATA[physical media]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            I was just paraphrasing.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Thanks to the total trash-fire that is modern audio mixing, it's become almost impossible to understand what anyone is saying in movies and TV shows. Which is why so many people who are not deaf or hard of hearing have started turning on the subtitles so they don't miss important plot points.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 15 Sep 2025 21:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/why-streaming-subtitles-are-always-slightly-wrong/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Qualcomm's Next Snapdragon Chipset Is Off To a Poor Start]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/qualcomm-next-snapdragon-chipset-is-off-to-a-poor-start/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Arol Wright]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/03a61de8.jpg" length="87252" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Android]]></category><category><![CDATA[Android Phones & Tablets]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            I'm sure it'll be fine. But why?
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Qualcomm doesn't seem to have quite figured out the naming scheme for its last few Snapdragon chips. Now, after the release of the Snapdragon 8 Elite, next year's chip will most certainly be a mouthful, as things are all up in the air now.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 15 Sep 2025 20:22:21 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/qualcomm-next-snapdragon-chipset-is-off-to-a-poor-start/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Microsoft Word, Excel, and PowerPoint's Copilot Integration Is Getting a Wider Rollout]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/microsoft-word-excel-and-powerpoints-copilot-integration-is-getting-a-wider-rollout/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jorge A. Aguilar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/office.jpg" length="135" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Microsoft]]></category><category><![CDATA[Microsoft 365 Personal]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Oh boy, more Copilot!
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Microsoft has rolled out Copilot Chat and its suite of AI agents to a wider audience, bringing the unified AI chat directly into Microsoft 365 apps. This is a big deal because the full-featured Copilot chat panel was only for those with a paid plan.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 15 Sep 2025 20:11:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/microsoft-word-excel-and-powerpoints-copilot-integration-is-getting-a-wider-rollout/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Your Power Supply Is a Ticking Time Bomb—Know the Warning Signs]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/your-power-supply-is-a-ticking-time-bombknow-the-warning-signs/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Sydney Butler]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/shutterstock_2034838052.jpg" length="596" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[pc building]]></category><category><![CDATA[PC Optimization]]></category><category><![CDATA[Hardware]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Pop goes the PC!
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>The Power Supply Unit (PSU) in your desktop computer is the beating heart of the system.Without power your computer is a paperweight, but just like a sudden heart attack can ruin your day, a worn-out or faulty PSU can scrap your whole computer permanently.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 15 Sep 2025 20:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/your-power-supply-is-a-ticking-time-bombknow-the-warning-signs/</guid></item></channel>
